history.content: I've taken a similar workload and thought it was doable. However, CS 61C and Stat 134 are pretty heavy classes conceptually, and although I haven't taken Math 104 yet, I've heard it's one of the hardest math courses here. It depends on what you want to get out of these classes, but I think you should go for it!

^ How does this schedule sound, if I were to enroll in an easier upper div. with a lower workload (I heard 168 has a small workload? the Internet class)? I've taken 134 until the drop deadline, so it's not like I'm completely in the dark. I haven't coded in about a year, though. Any advice? Thanks.
history.subject: Math 104, CS 61C, Stat 134 + CS Upper Div.
